            <div corresp="#c2948f2">
                <head>Act of Congress approved March 24, 1934. Sec. 8 913</head>
                <p>(3) Any Foreign Service officer may be assigned to duty in the Philippine
                    Islands, under a commission as a consular officer, for such period as may be
                    necessary and under such regulations as the Secretary of State may prescribe,
                    during which assignment such officer shall be considered as stationed in a
                    foreign country; but his powers and duties shall be confined to the performance
                    of such of the official acts and notarial and other services, which such officer
                    might properly perform in respect of the administration of the immigration laws
                    if assigned to a foreign country as a consular officer, as may be authorized by
                    the Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>(4) For the purposes of sections 18 and 20 of the Immigration Act of 1917, as
                    amended, the Philippine Islands shall be considered to be a foreign country.</p>
            </div>
